The paper introduces an alternative approach to Temporal Answer Set Programming, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The approach relies on Temporal Equilibrium Logic (TEL) for finite traces, which is a subfield of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of Answer Set Programming (ASP), which is a subfield of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper's focus on temporal modeling and reasoning suggests that it may also be relevant to Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DL).
